snippet.textDisplay: i love how everyone's starting to create theories while simultaneously acknowledging the "staged" or "planned" aspect of it all. this particular video is actually well-made suspense and tension-wise. the intentional goofy edits add to that "ha-ha it's just Unus and Annus messing around" but it also leaves that sense of panic at the back of the viewers' minds even if we know that most of this is probably staged anyway. the spacing of the silly and fuck-all videos and the more spooky or serious ones is chef's kiss this channel gives you a false sense of security and i'm all here for it!
snippet.textOriginal: i love how everyone's starting to create theories while simultaneously acknowledging the "staged" or "planned" aspect of it all. this particular video is actually well-made suspense and tension-wise. the intentional goofy edits add to that "ha-ha it's just Unus and Annus messing around" but it also leaves that sense of panic at the back of the viewers' minds even if we know that most of this is probably staged anyway. the spacing of the silly and fuck-all videos and the more spooky or serious ones is *chef's kiss* this channel gives you a false sense of security and i'm all here for it!

snippet.textDisplay: This would make a really good game I think. Like, imagine you’re a detective and your sent to investigate this house. You get a vision of what’s happening in this vid, but it’s incomplete. As you find more and more information and items it fills in. Until you know the truth.

snippet.textDisplay:
Co-Op horror game concept:





Same scenario, haunted room/building. A team of specialist must find the evil deity and exorcize it. One person plays as the investigator. The other person monitors the room. The monitor must feed back all information they get to the investigator and vice versa, however, there will be frequent moments of interference. They must overcome the complications and fear to get the mission done. If they fail, they die.
